race.comment: CHUR NIBBLE (5) made a mess of his rivals in maiden company two back when well supported. Followed it up with a strong effort at headquarters last time when beaten narrowly in a similar grade. Carries more weight this time but is cherry-ripe now and is sure to be getting involved. MRS PENNY CRACKER (11) is in terrific form. Flashed home to just miss to a progressive one last time at Gawler. Drawn kinder this time and will take plenty of stopping if she's close enough when straightening. COORONG TYCOON (1) finished second last start at the first run back from a spell at Murray Bridge. Strips fitter and has plenty of scope for improvement. MORLAIX (10) is a consistent performer with four minor placings from seven starts this prep. Turned in another good effort last time out when third at Oakbank. Holds claims on best figures. COLLATED (3) boasts a win over this track and trip. Watch for her charging late.
